question:
District category contains Silicon Valley, and Courthouse District.
Supermarkets category contains ShopRite, and Coles (Australia).
Product category contains Soda, and Flatbreads.
The number of each Coles (Australia) 's Soda equals 10 more than each ShopRite 's Product.
The number of each Courthouse District 's Coles (Australia) equals the sum of each ShopRite 's Flatbreads, each Coles (Australia) 's Soda, each ShopRite 's Product, and each Silicon Valley 's Coles (Australia).
The number of each Courthouse District 's ShopRite equals the sum of each Courthouse District 's Coles (Australia), each Silicon Valley 's Coles (Australia), and each ShopRite 's Flatbreads.
The number of each Silicon Valley 's Coles (Australia) equals 5.
The number of each ShopRite 's Flatbreads equals 5 more than each Silicon Valley 's Coles (Australia).
The number of each Silicon Valley 's ShopRite equals 21 times each Courthouse District 's Supermarkets.
How many ShopRite does Silicon Valley have?
solution:
Define each Silicon Valley 's Coles (Australia) as o; So o = 5.
Define each ShopRite 's Flatbreads as R; So R = 5 + o = 5 + 5 = 10.
Define each ShopRite 's Product as M; So M = R = 10.
Define each Coles (Australia) 's Soda as H; So H = 10 + M = 10 + 10 = 20.
Define each Courthouse District 's Coles (Australia) as N; P = M + R = 10 + 10 = 20; z = P + o = 20 + 5 = 2; So N = H + z = 20 + 2 = 22.
Define each Courthouse District 's ShopRite as v; i = o + R = 5 + 10 = 15; So v = N + i = 22 + 15 = 14.
Define each Courthouse District 's Supermarkets as B; So B = v + N = 14 + 22 = 13.
Define each Silicon Valley 's ShopRite as r; So r = 21 * B = 21 * 13 = 20.
